<HTML>
<HEAD>
<TITLE>
Newly Elected IAEA Board of Governors 
</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR=#ffffff>
<HR>
<B>19 September 1996
<BR>
PR 96/20
<BR>
General Conference
</B>
<CENTER>
<H2>
Newly Elected IAEA Board of Governors </H2>
</CENTER>
<P>
<HR>
<P>
The 40th regular session of the International Atomic Energy Agency's General
         Conference has elected 11 Member States to the IAEA Board of Governors, the 35-member policy-making body.
<P>         
         The 11 Member States newly elected to the Board are Argentina, Belgium,
         Colombia, Cuba, Czech Republic, Malaysia, Namibia, New Zealand, Portugal,
         Tunisia, and United Arab Emirates.
       <P>  
         The other 24 Member States of the Board which have either been designated
         by the Board of Governors or elected by the General Conference are: Australia,
         Brazil, Bulgaria, Canada, Chile, China, Denmark, Egypt, France, Germany, India,
         Japan, Republic of Korea, Kuwait, Netherlands, Nicaragua, Nigeria, Romania,
         Russian Federation, Saudi Arabia, South Africa, Switzerland, United Kingdom of
         Great Britain and Northern Ireland, and United States of America.
         <P>
         The newly-constituted Board will convene on 23 September, following the
         conclusion of the General Conference, to elect the Board Chairman and Vice
         Chairmen for the period 1996-1997.
<P>
         <HR>
<CENTER>
<P>
Back to <A HREF="index.html">Listing of Press Releases</A>
<P>
</CENTER>
<HR>
<P>
</BODY>
</HTML>

