<HTML>
<HEAD>
   <TITLE>GC-40 President Biodata</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY>
<P><TABLE BORDER=0 CELLPADDING=1 WIDTH="600">
   <TR>
      <TD VALIGN=TOP WIDTH=160>
         <P><IMG SRC="gcpres.jpg" WIDTH=160 HEIGHT=221 ALIGN=left>
      </TD>
      <TD VALIGN=TOP>
         <H2 ALIGN=CENTER>Dr. William G. Padolina</H2>
         
         <H3 ALIGN=CENTER>Secretary</H3>
         
         <H3 ALIGN=CENTER>Department of Science and Technology</H3>
         
         <H3 ALIGN=CENTER>Republic of the Philippines</H3>
      </TD></TR>
</TABLE>
<P>&nbsp;
<P>Dr. Padolina has been Secretary (Minister ) of Science and
Technology of the Philippines since 7 July 1994. Before that, he was
an Undersecretary in the Department of Science and Technology
responsible for Research and Development.
<P>Dr. Padolina is also a Professor of Chemistry in the University of
the Philippines. Los Ba&ntilde;os (UPLB) form 1988 to 1991 and Director of
the National Institute of Biotechnology and Applied Microbiolgy from
1986 to 1990.
<P>He is an Academician of the National Academy of Science and
Technology. He was chosen by the Academy in 1982 as an Outstanding
Young Scientist in the field of phytochemistry. He was chosen in 1985
as one of the Ten Outstanding Young Men for Science and Technology.
<P>He is Co-chairman of the Nuclear Power Steering Committee, an
inter-agency body created by the President of the Philippines for the
purpose of preparing a nuclear energy programme. He was Chairman of
the Committee on Science and Technology of the Association of
Southeast Asian Nations (ASEAN) in 1994.
<P>He is the author of 45 publications in refereed journals in
natural products, chemistry, biotechnology and coconut chemistry.
<P>Dr. Padolina graduated <I>Magna cum Laude</I> from the University of the
Philippines, Los Ba&ntilde;os, in 1968 with the degree of Bachelor of
Science in Agricultural Chemistry. He obtained his Ph.D. in Botany
and Phytochemistry from the University of Texas in 1973.
<P>He was born on 15 November 1946, is married, and has three
children.
<P>
