<TITLE>Other IAEA Internet services</TITLE>
</head>
<body>
<h2>Other IAEA Internet Services</h2>
<p>In addition to the IAEA's Web-base family of Internet products, 
the Agency offers a number of other Internet-based services.
<hr>
<dl>
<dt><A HREF="mailto:info@iaea.or.at">E-mail Information</A>
<dd>For privacy reasons, IAEA has removed access to the on-line
e-mail address directory.  Please send any enquiries to the above
e-mail address.<p>
<dt><strong><a href="ftp://ftp.iaea.or.at/pub">FTP</a>:</strong>
<dd>The FTP server has the following data:
<ul>
<li> <a href="ftp://ftp.iaea.or.at/pub/gnip">GNIP (Global Network for Isotopes 
in Precipitation) Data</a>.  See also
the related <a href=/programs/ri/>descriptions in our WWW pages</a>.  

<li> <a href="ftp://nesirs01.iaea.or.at/pub/web-browsers/">WWW browsing tools</a> 

<li> <a href="ftp://ftp.iaea.or.at/pub/vacancy_posts">Vacancy Notices</a>
<li> <a href="ftp://ftp.iaea.or.at/pub/agris/agrisinf">AGRIS Information</a>
<li> <a href="ftp://ftp.iaea.or.at/pub/safis/">IAEA databases on safety issues of WWER and RBMK 
reactors</a>.  The files can be used with a password provided by the IAEA to registered technical organizations 
of the Member states involved in the related IAEA projects.  For further information 
please e-mail <a href="mailto:czibolya@nepo1.iaea.or.at">Mr. Laszlo Czibolya</a>.
</ul>

<dt><strong><a href="gopher://nesirs01.iaea.or.at">Gopher</a>:</strong>
<dd>Here you will find references to the <a href="gopher://gopher.iaea.or.at/11/main/inis">INIS.</a>   
<br><strong>Please note</strong>: some of the information previously available on the gopher, such as the 
<a href="/worldatom/vacancies/">IAEA Vacancy Announcements</a>, is now 
accessible only at the IAEA's WWW server.
<p>
<dt><strong>Usenet
<a href="news://news.iaea.or.at">discussion groups</a>:
</strong>
<dd><i>available only for IAEA staff</i>
 
<dt><strong><a href="/htdocs/onlinedb.html">
IAEA Databases and Information Resources</a>:</strong><dd>Access to online references 
and databases
</dl>

<h3>Links to selected other Internet servers:</h3>
<dl>
<dt>List of servers in the UN family maintained at:
<ul>
<LI><A HREF="http://www.unsystem.org">Official Web Site Locator</A> for the 
United Nations System of Organizations 
<li><A HREF="http://www.unicc.org">UN International Computing Centre</a> 
in Geneva
<li><a href="http://www.undcp.org/unlinks.html">UN Drug Control Programme</a> in Vienna
</ul>
<p>
<!dt}Link to 
{a href="http://ravel.ifs.univie.ac.at/austria/wien.html"}Vienna{/a} pages.>

</dl>

<p>It is also planned to provide X.500 directory service covering <em>
Persons, Organizational units, Locations and Information resources<em>.  
