<TD valign=top>
    <IMG SRC="/worldatom/images/hline.gif">
</TD>
<TD VALIGN=top>

<img src="/worldatom/images/board_sm.gif" align="right" height="81" width="150">
The IAEA Board Committee considering further measures for <b><tt><a href="/GC/gc40/documents/gc40-17.html">STRENGTHENING NUCLEAR SAFEGUARDS</a></b></tt> will hold its third session 
in early 1997, beginning 20 January at the Agency's headquarters in Vienna. The Committee specifically is negotiating a legal instrument required for the introduction of 
verification measures that go beyond the IAEA's authority under existing comprehensive safeguards agreements concluded with States. The latest edition of the <i><a 
href="/worldatom/inforesource/bulletin/bull384/">IAEA Bulletin </a></i> features articles describing the safeguards development programme and the Agency's experience so far in 
introducing some new measures that the Board already has approved. For a full listing of the nuclear facilities and locations under IAEA safeguards around the world, see the <a 
href="/worldatom/program/safeguards/95tables/facilities.html">listings</a> in the IAEA <a href="/worldatom/inforesource/annual/anrep95/">Annual Report</a>.
<br clear="right">
<br>
<b><tt>FACTS ABOUT THE WORLD'S USE of NUCLEAR POWER</b></tt> for electricity generation -- and associated environmental and economic benefits -- were emphasized by IAEA Director 
General Hans Blix in Manila recently. Speaking at the Second Philippine Nuclear Congress, Dr. Blix said that the world's greater use of nuclear power could "significantly alleviate 
the dilemma of an increasing need for energy and an increasing need to reduce carbon dioxide emissions". The <a href="/worldatom/inforesource/dgspeeches/dgsp1996n14.html">full 
text</a> of his address, as well as the <a href="/worldatom/inforesource/dgspeeches/dgsp1996n15.html">text of a lecture</a> he gave on nuclear applications in medical and other 
fields, are now on line.
<br>
<br>
Preliminary information about <b><tt><a href="/worldatom/thisweek/preview/">SCIENTIFIC AND TECHNICAL MEETINGS</a></b></tt> being convened by the IAEA during the coming year is 
available. The month-to-month listings include titles, dates and venues.
<br>
<br>
<i><b>WorldAtom's</b></i> pages now feature <b><tt><a href="/worldatom/infcircs/">IAEA INFORMATION CIRCULARS (INFCIRCS)</a></b></tt>, documents that the Agency regularly issues to 
its 124 Member States on a range of nuclear topics and developments.
<br>
<br>
<img src="/worldatom/images/inisindex.gif" align="left" width="72" height="71">
<b><tt>LOOKING FOR NUCLEAR INFORMATION?</b></tt> Check the range of references in the IAEA's <a href="/programmes/inis/inis.htm">International Nuclear Information System (INIS)</a>, 
the world's largest bibliographic reference source in the nuclear field.
<br>
<br clear="left">
<p>
