<TITLE>Technical Cooperation Home Page</TITLE></HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR=#C0DCC0>
<center><h2>Welcome to</h2><img align=bottom src="images/tcearth.gif"></center>
<blockquote>The primary objective of the IAEA's technical co-operation programme is to assist Member States in achieving self-reliance in applications of nuclear science and technology.<P> The IAEA, in co-operation with its Member States, yearly supports over 1000 development projects in nuclear science and technology. Technical experts are sent to counterpart institutes as advisers and lecturers, group and individual training is provided at leading institutes around the world, and equipment is supplied for research and development projects in the field.<P>Through these and other avenues, the technological tools, skills and experience important to the safe utilisation of nuclear techniques are provided to developing Member States, thus enabling the benefits of such techniques to have a lasting impact on sustainable human development.</blockquote>
<HR ALIGN=center SIZE=2><H3><B>Current topics:</B></H3>
